What you described is the way to simplify rational expression. You have given a very clear example. The only minor correction is the first step: here we are not looking for the greatest common denominator (we need that when we add two fractions),  instead we want to find the greatest common factor of the numerator and the denominator, and 6x^4 is the GCF.\par
